    <text xml:id="Site_WFY_Section_Db_Cave70">
        <body>
            <div type="cave" xml:lang="zh">
                <head type="cave">
                    <hi rend="bold">70</hi>號窟</head>
                <div>
                    <head>描述</head>
                    <div>
                        <head>概述</head>
                        <p>該窟未刊刻經文，且窟頂較低，但最初可能作爲經窟開鑿。窟内刊刻一則北宋開寶七年（974/975）妝修願文，但該窟造像呈現8世紀風格（<ptr target="WFY_70_2007_w70-0.jpg"/>）。<!--願文如下：“修粧釋迦牟尼佛部眾一龕，修造遮佛龕厦舍一面，弟子馮崇夫婦同發心，為女弟子劉氏不安，願獲平善，希獲平善。開寶七年十一月十八日（975年1月3日），設齋表慶了酬，求章福祚。”-->
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <head>位置</head>
                        <list>
                            <item>位於南崖，<foreign xml:lang="en">D</foreign>區。窟底距現今步道約230厘米。 </item>
                            <item>該窟位於<hi rend="bold">65</hi>號窟以東280厘米處，窟内地面與<hi rend="bold">65</hi>號窟平齊，但二者之間相隔一溝壑，近期已填充石塊進行加固。該窟東距<foreign xml:lang="en">E</foreign>區<hi rend="bold">71</hi>號窟51厘米，後者窟内地面高出前者93厘米。</item>
                            <item>
                                <foreign xml:lang="en">f</foreign>壁方向：326˚</item>
                        </list>
                        <p/>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <head>形制</head>
                        <p>敞口方形窟，進深祗及其他洞窟一半，d壁和f壁經過打磨，正壁<foreign xml:lang="en">e</foreign>壁雕一鋪七尊像。繪有垂直花卉紋飾帶自窟頂沿d壁與f壁延伸至窟底。<foreign xml:lang="en">d</foreign>壁中部、裝飾帶外側，刊刻一則尺寸爲40×20厘米的妝修願文（<ptr target="WFY_070_d_colophon_DSC_2541.jpg"/>）。</p>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <head>尺寸</head>
                        <list>
                            <item>
                                <foreign xml:lang="en">d</foreign>壁：前部高164厘米，寬140厘米。</item>
                            <item>
                                <foreign xml:lang="en">e</foreign>壁：寬178厘米。</item>
                            <item>
                                <foreign xml:lang="en">f</foreign>壁：前部高164厘米，中部寬140厘米<!--，但底部近地面處寬95厘米-->。</item>
                            <item>窟口：寬169厘米。</item>
                        </list>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div xml:id="Site_WFY_Section_Db_Cave70_discussion_zh">
                    <head>討論</head>
                    <bibl>
                            彭家勝<ref type="biblio" target="Pengjiasheng1988">第3－4頁，第5頁</ref>
                        <note>
                            <p>彭家勝提及正壁七尊像以及<foreign xml:lang="en">d</foreign>壁北宋開寶七年（974/975）妝修題記。
                                </p>
                        </note>
                    </bibl>
                    <bibl>
                            曹丹<ref type="biblio" target="Caodan1990">第49頁</ref>
                        <note>
                            <p>曹丹分析正壁七尊像，認爲其風格接近廣元千佛崖同類造像。
                                </p>
                        </note>
                    </bibl>
                    <bibl>
                            胡文和<ref type="biblio" target="Huwenhe1992">第5頁</ref>
                        <note>
                            <p>胡文和描述七尊像的一些細部，亦提及北宋開寶七年（974/975）妝修題記。</p>
                        </note>
                    </bibl>
                    <bibl>
                            鄧之金<ref type="biblio" target="Dengzhijin1993">第37頁</ref>
                        <note>
                            <p>鄧之金迻録了北宋開寶七年十一月十八日（975年1月3日）妝修題記，并提供其測量數據。</p>
                            <p/>
                        </note>
                    </bibl>
                    <bibl>
                            李良和鄧之金<ref type="biblio" target="Li_Deng1997">第43頁</ref>
                        <note>
                            <p>作者提供洞窟的測量數據，并根據風格將洞窟年代定在開元年間（713－741）。他們也提及宋代的妝修活動，并迻録北宋開寶七年十一月十八日（975年1月3日）的題記。</p>
                        </note>
                    </bibl>
                    <bibl>
                        秦臻、張雪芬和雷玉華<ref type="biblio" target="Qin_Zhang_Lei2015">第92－93頁</ref>
                        <note>
                            <p>作者詳細描述了洞窟的地理位置、建築形制以及造像龕和各尊像，并迻録<foreign xml:lang="en">d</foreign>壁上的妝修題記。</p>
                        </note>
                    </bibl>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <figure rend="center" n="figure" xml:id="WFY_70_2007_w70-0.jpg">
                        <head xml:lang="zh">
                            <hi rend="bold">70</hi>號窟仰視全景。2007年拍攝</head>
                        <head>Full view of cave <hi rend="bold">70</hi> from below; photograph taken in 2007
                        </head>
                        <graphic url="WFY_70_2007_w70-0.jpg"/>
                    </figure>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="cave" xml:lang="en">
                <head type="cave">
                    <hi rend="bold">Cave 70</hi>
                </head>
                <div>
                    <head>Description</head>
                    <div>
                        <head>Overview</head>
                        <p>The cave does not contain sutras, but may have been planned as a sutra cave, although it is very low. It has a votive inscription of 975, but its figures show an eighth century style (fig. <ptr target="WFY_70_2007_w70-0.jpg"/>).
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <head>Location</head>
                        <list>
                            <item>Southern slope, section D, ca. 230 cm above present walkway. </item>
                            <item>The cave is 280 cm east of cave <hi rend="bold">65</hi>, whose floor is at the same level, but which is separated by a vertical canyon that has recently been fortified and filled with stones. It is separated by 51 cm from cave <hi rend="bold">71</hi>, in section E to the east, with a floor 93 cm higher than that of cave <hi rend="bold">70</hi>.</item>
                            <item>Direction: wall f: 326°.</item>
                        </list>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <head>Shape</head>
                        <p>Box shape with open front. The cave is only about half as deep as other sutra caves. Walls d and f are polished, but carved on its rear wall e is the usual group of seven figures. Vertical ornamental bands with painted flower motifs run from the ceiling to the floor on walls d and f. The votive inscription, measuring 40 x 20 cm, is placed in the middle of wall d, outside the ornamental band (fig. <ptr target="WFY_070_d_colophon_DSC_2541.jpg"/>).</p>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <head>Measurements</head>
                        <list>
                            <item>Wall d: height at the front 164 cm, width 140 cm.</item>
                            <item>Wall e: width 178 cm.</item>
                            <item>Wall f: height at the front 164 cm, width 140 cm (middle)<!--, but 95 cm at the floor-->.</item>
                            <item>Width of front opening 169 cm.</item>
                        </list>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div xml:id="Site_WFY_Section_Db_Cave70_discussion_en">
                    <head>Discussion</head>
                    <bibl>
                        <ref type="biblio" target="Pengjiasheng1988">3–4, 5</ref>
                        <note>
                            <p>Peng Jiasheng mentions the group of seven figures on the rear wall, and the colophon on wall d about a restoration made in the seventh year of the <hi rend="italic">kaibao </hi>
                                <foreign xml:lang="zh">開寶</foreign> era of the Northern Song dynasty (974/975).
                            </p>
                        </note>
                    </bibl>
                    <bibl>
                        <ref type="biblio" target="Caodan1990">49</ref>
                        <note>
                            <p>Cao Dan gives a description of the group of seven figures carved on the rear wall, and says that their style is comparable to figures at the Thousand Buddha Cliff <foreign xml:lang="zh">千佛崖</foreign> in Guangyuan <foreign xml:lang="zh">廣元</foreign>.
                            </p>
                        </note>
                    </bibl>
                    <bibl>
                        <ref type="biblio" target="Huwenhe1992">3, 5</ref>
                        <note>
                            <p>Hu Wenhe describes the group of seven figures in some detail, and also mentions the colophon about the restoration of 974/975.</p>
                        </note>
                    </bibl>
                    <bibl>
                        <ref type="biblio" target="Dengzhijin1993">37</ref>
                        <note>
                            <p>Deng Zhijin provides measurements and a transcription of the colophon dated to the seventh year of the <hi rend="italic">kaibao </hi>
                                <foreign xml:lang="zh">開寶</foreign> era, ascribing it erroneously to the year 974.</p>
                            <p/>
                        </note>
                    </bibl>
                    <bibl>
                        <ref type="biblio" target="HuWenhe1994">62</ref>
                        <note>
                            <p>Hu Wenhe basically repeats the information given in <ref type="biblio" target="Huwenhe1992">3, 5</ref>.
                                
                            </p>
                        </note>
                    </bibl>
                    <bibl>
                        <ref type="biblio" target="Li_Deng1997">43</ref>
                        <note>
                            <p>The authors give measurements and date the cave to the <hi rend="italic">kaiyuan</hi> era on stylistic grounds. They also mention repairs and the new decoration of the Song dynasty and give a full transcription of the colophon of January 3, 975.</p>
                        </note>
                    </bibl>
                    <bibl>
                        <ref type="biblio" target="ChengduKaoguFaxian2008">384–386</ref>
                        <note>
                            <p>The editors of the Chengdu Municipal Institute of Cultural Relics and Archaeology describe the niche and all seven statues in great detail, and they provide equally detailed measurements. They also transcribe the accompanying colophon.</p>
                        </note>
                    </bibl>
                    <bibl>
                        <ref type="biblio" target="LeeSonyaS2009">41; 46; 73, note 17</ref>
                        <note>
                            <p>Lee includes niche <hi rend="bold">70</hi> in her cluster V, which corresponds to section E. She identifies the main seated Buddha as <foreign xml:lang="sa">Śākyamuni</foreign> and says that the style of this figure’s halo was used throughout the Grove and can be found at all clusters.  </p>
                        </note>
                    </bibl>
                    <bibl>
                        <ref type="biblio" target="Qin_Zhang_Lei2015">92–93</ref>
                        <note>
                            <p>The authors give detailed descriptions of the location and the architecture of the cave, as well as of the niche as a whole and of each sculpture. They provide a transcription of the colophon on wall d.</p>
                        </note>
                    </bibl>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <figure rend="center" n="figure" xml:id="WFY_caves_70-72_DSC_0208.jpg">
                        <head xml:lang="zh">
                            <hi rend="bold">70</hi>號窟及相鄰<foreign xml:lang="en">E</foreign>區。2010年拍攝</head>
                        <head>Cave <hi rend="bold">70</hi> and the adjacent section E; photograph taken in 2010
                            </head>
                        <graphic url="WFY_caves_70-72_DSC_0208.jpg"/>
                    </figure>
                </div>
            </div>
